  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Peanut Butter Brownies. An American family-table recipe — generous, comforting, built for a crowd. Adjustable for what you need."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Cookies bake fast and reward a chilled dough. Pull them out when the edges set and the middles still look slightly underdone."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "What you need"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "attrs": {
          "defaultServings": 4,
          "items": [
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "peanut-butter",
              "amount": 225,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": "vegan or regular",
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "dark-chocolate",
              "amount": 200,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": "vegan or regular",
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "light-brown-sugar",
              "amount": 280,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "eggs",
              "amount": 3,
              "unit": "each",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            },
            {
              "ingredientSlug": "self-raising-flour",
              "amount": 100,
              "unit": "g",
              "prepNote": null,
              "isOptional": false,
              "groupLabel": null
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Method"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Set aside 50g each of the peanut butter and chocolate."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Heat oven to 180C/160C fan/gas 4 and line a 20cm square baking tin with baking parchment."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Gently melt remaining peanut butter, chocolate and all the sugar in a pan, stirring occasionally, until the sugar has just about melted."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Turn off heat and use a wooden spoon to beat in the eggs one by one."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Stir in the flour and scrape into the tin."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Melt reserved peanut butter in the microwave on High for 45 secs, or in a pan, until runny, then drizzle over the brownie."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Bake for 30-35 mins until it has a crust, but the middle still seems slightly uncooked."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Melt reserved chocolate, drizzle over the brownie, then cool in the tin before cutting into squares."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "heading": "If something goes wrong",
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "symptom": "Mixture won't set",
              "cause": "Sugar didn't reach the right stage, or temperature was guessed.",
              "fix": "Use a sugar thermometer. Stages: soft-ball 115°C, hard-ball 125°C, soft-crack 135°C, hard-crack 150°C. Cold-water tests work but the thermometer doesn't lie."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Sugar crystallised",
              "cause": "Mixture stirred after it started bubbling, or a stray crystal landed on the side of the pan.",
              "fix": "Don't stir once the sugar is dissolved. Brush the inside of the pan with a wet pastry brush to wash crystals down."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Fudge is grainy",
              "cause": "Beaten too soon — while still too hot.",
              "fix": "Cool to 43°C before beating. The mixture turns from glossy to matte when ready to set."
            },
            {
              "symptom": "Mixture seized into a ball",
              "cause": "Water touched melted chocolate.",
              "fix": "Add a teaspoon of warm cream or water and stir until smooth — this is the trick. Drier seizing needs more liquid; thin seizing wants less."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Variations"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Flavoured version: stir in a teaspoon of vanilla, almond, or peppermint extract once the mixture is off the heat."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Dip-coated: once set, dip pieces in melted dark chocolate and let drip on baking paper."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Make ahead, freezing, leftovers"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best fresh. Leftovers keep two days in the fridge; reheat covered with a splash of liquid."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Where this dish lives"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "A classic American home recipe — generous, comforting, made for a crowd. The proportions are heartier than the British equivalent; the method is built for a Sunday afternoon."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
